    <h2>Why you should hire me:</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="rightcol">
    <h3>I understand the complexity of building businesses that are both sustainable and positively impact the world.</h3>
    <p>
     I worked for an entrepreneurship center in Rwanda where I got a strong dose of humility after struggling to see the impacts of a year of effort. We had been trying to teach entrepreneurship to high school students in rural parts of East Africa, but it was clear they weren't absorbing our curriculum. After reexamining the problem we were trying to solve (lack of economic mobility and growth), we realized that before we taught the technical skills of entrepreneurship, we needed to change the lack of self-efficacy in those regions, which was perpetuated by rural African culture and Western aid. First-hand experiences like these give me a framework for understanding the needs of the Unreasonable ecosystem, which will allow me to help build a platform that addresses their most pressing issues and stresses.
    </p>
    <h3>I thrive off turning seemingly confusing and disjointed data into something usable.</h3>
    <p>
       The first time I saw the potential impact of data was in 2013 when I was put in charge of 'proving' the benefits of a solar power program in Fort Portal, Uganda. The only issue was that the organization was not selling the power systems, they were giving them away, which meant very little financial data to work with. So I looked for other metrics, eventually building an SROI (social return on investment) model to present the economic, social, and emotional benefits of solar power for people in poverty. I am excited at the prospect of building a quantitative and qualitative model for the ventures in the Unreasonable Group ecosystem and using my skills in d3.js to help those ventures understand their KPIs.
    </p>
    <h3>I will create a strong synergy with the UX/UI designer on this project.</h3>
    <p>
       Aside from the various front end development skills I have (see a list on my resume), I also completed a UX/UI program where I delved into user surveys, building personas, A/B testing, high-fidelity mock-ups, and clickable prototypes. Although development is my forte, my UX/UI skills will allow me to create a dynamic and symbiotic collaboration with the UX designer on board. I believe strongly that the right people working together are more than a sum of their parts.
    </p>
    <h3>I've got the fire, baby!</h3>
    <p>
       What makes me unique is my zeal, my limitless energy towards current passions. When I decide to do something, I pursue it with 100% conviction. This position with Unreasonable is one of those times when I can barely contain the energy that is building about creating this platform.
    </p>
